  "description": "PSNR delta of the gsplat-based differentiable repack pass vs naive opacity-prune at the same byte budget. Algorithm lives in splatforge-private; reproducing the numbers requires the proprietary build + ~$0.10/scene of A100 spot time. Values are published; the optimizer is not. N=5 seed medians \u00b1 stdev. Honest failure modes: transparency (median -8.30 dB) and floater (median -2.23 dB) regress against opacity-prune at the same byte budget.",
  "version": "0.1.1-v4-baseline-n5",
  "target_ratio": 0.5,
  "approach": "gsplat 1.5.3 + self-distillation against 32 inside-the-cloud orbit-camera pseudo-photos (192px); hard-prune by saliency (alpha * |sigma scale|) every N iters; v0.1.1 additions: (1) gated Beer-Lambert opacity compensation rescales \u03b1 to preserve integrated transmittance (1-\u03b1_new) = (1-\u03b1_old)^(N_old/N_new) when surviving cohort mean \u03b1 < 0.4; (2) alpha-channel MSE supervision alongside RGB-MSE during training \u2014 the rasterizer already returns per-pixel \u03b1; supervising it gives the optimizer a direct signal for volume composition that RGB-MSE saturates over. Alpha-loss weight is tapered by baseline alpha distribution.",
